# Character List: Chapters 01-24

This document was prepared by Claude Code and edited by John for accuracy. It's mostly accurate.

## Main Characters

**Reginald Metcalf Digsxby** - Retired flying island resident with a private island (Ithaca); married to Francesca; lost his right hand in The Great War of Succession and Mirth in Barcelona; paranoid about betrayal; mysteriously disappeared after being knocked unconscious

**Francesca "Fran" "Franny" "'Cesca" (sometimes "Eleanor") Metcalf Digsxby** - Reginald's wife; skilled ventriloquist and copy-editress; had an emotional affair with Dr. Michaelmas Term; involved in Reginald's mysterious disappearance

**Thomas Metcalf** - Intuitive Detective who can follow "the Track"; woke on January 1st with premonition of death; cousin to Paul Eeny

**Martinius J. Kijller** - The Martini Killer; ophthalmologist by trade; lives at 123 Malibu Lane; former childhood bedwetter; has a distinctive pin shaped like a martini on his lapel; Thursday is his day off; originally Dutch; his wife Gloria died in an accident he could not prevent; he was subsequently resurrected/recruited by the Three Voices; had a "don't kill your wife juice" dependency that suppressed violent urges; incapacitated on Jan 3 when Thomas remotely tampered with his MART.INI file

**The Beach Detective** - Works for Lars Squiggle; returning to flying island on assignment regarding the Digsxbys; prefers sunshine; mostly prefers women but makes occasional exceptions

## Police/Detectives

**Blarte Canche** - Malle Cop (senior police officer); partner to Baba Waters

**Baba Waters** - Police officer; partner to Blarte Canche

**Georgia Mann** - Unintuitive Detective; married to Florida Mann; investigating connection between multiple deaths including Dr. Michaelmas Term, Archbishop Winterpipe, and Georg Smelv

**Wright Heare** - Detective; Georgia Mann's first partner; killed by the Martini Killer

**Wleft Theare** - Wright Heare's identical twin brother; became Georgia's partner after Wright's death; killed by the Martini Killer (strangled with breeches, hung from lamppost)

**Wmiddle Yone** - Identical twin brother of Wleft Theare; also a detective; killed by the Martini Killer (found stuffed full of olives)

## Supporting Characters

**Manuel Ordinator Computer Gonzalez** - Reginald's manservant; appears to be a robot but is actually a human in a robot suit; meticulous researcher

**Paul Eeny (Paul Metcalf Eeny)** - Martin Eeny's "gay lover" (euphoric aficionado); calls his intuitive sense "the Groove"; Thomas's cousin from the continental side of the family; homosexual but chaste; gave Regular Belasco an envelope of photos for Thomas on Tuesday evening; **confirmed dead** (killed between Jan 1 and Jan 3; last known location 1440 Ratcliffe Court; killer unknown)

**Lars Squiggle** - Teacher at Wilhelmchester School for Boys; often considered a founding father of modern continentalism; had shot knees from grashing; mysteriously disappeared in year 0x8eb; employs the beach detective; lives on a beach (Da Nang or similar)

**Hilbert Milbert Mavid (H.M.M.) Digsxby** - Reginald's father; "the elder Digsxby"; rollercoaster tycoon; lost ability to speak clearly after an accident that also cost him both legs; married to Marigold Sunshine Digsxby

**Prudence Wellesley** - Waitress at a cafe; gave Thomas a massage; Thomas fell for her; invited to dinner at the Mann household; working undercover as a barista at Reginald's secret aerobike hangar ("Le Calcul de l'Écume") on Jan 3; appears to be some kind of agent (has briefing materials, reports to the detectives)

**"Marvinlust Maoi"** - Mysterious stranger on the aeroömnibus; cheerful; offered pills; pretended to be a cowboy at the zoo; claimed not to eat cheeses

**Bus "the Gherkin" Gurton (also called Gurton Buster, GurBus, Gherk Buston)** - Thomas's partner; unaccountably lucky; has a fresh, mild flavor; wandered into Martinius's lair through a secret tunnel

**Florida Mann** - Georgia Mann's husband; father to Louis and Tex; descendant of Tramar Lacel Dillard

## Minor Characters

**Martin Eeny** - Killed on December 31st when Reginald's martini glass fell on his head from the flying island above; had the ear of the Imperial Aviation Administration

**Mai Friend** - Woman found dead in her home with body torn apart in shape of a martini glass; discovered by Thomas on January 1st

**Dr. Michaelmas Juliet Term** - Famous zeppeliner/dirigible pilot (presumed deceased); died in a dirigible crash approximately 3 years ago; had many admiresses; Francesca was a passenger in both of his crashes; his body was never found; noted for his warmth, love for all mankind, and ability to bench 300 pounds

**Bartimieus Ender** - Bartender at the Metropolitan Cafe; killed by the Martini Killer (according to Martinius)

**Ernest Lyle Dransdorf** - Bartender who had reservations at Chez Foie; serializes elopements

**"Louis" Louisiana Mann** - Florida's older son (by two years)

**"Tex" Texas Mann** - Florida's younger son; hasn't mastered his tongue yet

**Johann "Yo" Deller** - Yodeler at the zoo; easily startled

**"Pointy Shoes" Dugan** - Shopkeeper who sold the beach detective breeches

**Bertrand "Berty" h’Ateaux** - Reginald’s friend; has a valet called "Machine"; arranged to meet Reginald at sea level after his escape

**Regular "Reggie" Belasco** - The fat man; somewhat world-weary; brought Thomas an envelope of photos from Paul Eeny on Jan 3 morning; knew Paul Eeny; fled when the shooting started

**Vanessa "Maneater" Bonë Whîte** - Blind female assassin; has "ovniscience" — a supernatural uterine third sight that locates fecund males when ovulating; carries a gun named Tiffany (Mburu-Braun T59) and travels by stealth helicopter; hired to kill Thomas (and possibly others); ultimately spared him and told him Paul Eeny's last known location (1440 Ratcliffe Court)

**Gloria Undine Kijller** - Martinius's late wife; died accidentally (broken neck, slipped on icy steps); Martinius had been attempting suicide to protect her from himself when it happened; may have met Lars Squiggle in the Backrooms before her marriage to Martinius

**The Three Voices (First, Second, Third)** - Mysterious figures who resurrected/recruited Martinius after Gloria's death; asked him about the principles behind the flying islands' suspension

## Mentioned "Characters"

**Marigold Sunshine Digsxby** - H.M.M. Digsxby's wife

**Dick** - Played island-golf with Reginald

**Georg Smelv** - Tobacconist from East Dulwich; found asphyxiated with a balloon animal

**Archbishop Winterpipe** - Pushed off a bridge last winter

**Arthur Fox** - Name Thomas used to get prescription on April 8th, 'd2

**Rachel, Arbo, Gleeson** - Cousins who played with Thomas and Paul at Uncle Fresno's ranch Christmas 0x8ed

**Uncle Fresno** - Owned a ranch where the Metcalf family gathered for Christmas 0x8ed

**Barley** - Friend of "Pointy Shoes" Dugan; owns a breech shop. Probably the one who kicked Thomas in the ribs as he lay dying.

**Hugo Wright** - Identical twin half-cousin to Wright Heare.

**Jerry** - Dishwasher at the cafe where Thomas ate

**Enronia** - Dr. Michaelmas Term's lover

**Gary Mandarin** - Noted sonnetier

**The whelp/shopchild/shopcritter** - Tended the newsstand

**The Newsie** - Newspaper seller who told the beach detective about Wmiddle Yone's death. Same as the shopcritter above????

**Lord Fitzthistlewits** - Mayor-for-life of Skoios; handsome and humble; appears in photos (holding a martini glass at various parties) that Paul Eeny left for Thomas; some connection to the Martini Killer case that the fat man considers "obvious" (but which Thomas hasn't yet figured out)

## Deaths

### Confirmed Martini Killer victims
- **Mai Friend** - body found Jan 1; killed in martini glass shape
- **Bartimieus Ender** - bartender at Metropolitan Cafe; Martinius confirmed it
- **Wright Heare** - killed Jan 2 (~12:30pm)
- **Wleft Theare** - killed Jan 2 evening; strangled with martini-patterned breeches, hung from lamppost
- **Wmiddle Yone** - killed Jan 2/3; stuffed full of olives

### Other deaths
- **Martin Eeny** - Dec 31; accident (Reginald's martini glass); not a Martini Killer victim
- **Paul Eeny** - killed between Jan 1 and Jan 3; last known location 1440 Ratcliffe Court; killer unknown
- **Gloria Undine Kijller** - years before main story; accidental (broken neck on icy steps)
- **Archbishop Winterpipe** - last winter; pushed off a bridge; killer unclear (Georgia Mann suspects Francesca)
- **Georg Smelv** - tobacconist; asphyxiated with balloon animal; killer unclear (Georgia Mann suspects Francesca)
- **Dr. Michaelmas Term** - ~3 years before main story; dirigible crash; body never found; circumstances unclear

## Organizations/Groups

**The Continents/Continentalists** - Political faction opposed to the flying islands

**Imperial Aviation Administration** - Regulatory body Martin Eeny had influence with

**The Whisk Boys** - Colloquial name for forensics department members
